00:17:28.205 --> 00:17:30.456 A:middle
On iOS 11, Safari View

00:17:30.456 --> 00:17:31.786 A:middle
Controller will have a separate

00:17:31.786 --> 00:17:34.156 A:middle
persistent data store in each

00:17:34.476 --> 00:17:35.596 A:middle
app that it's used in.

00:17:36.326 --> 00:17:38.176 A:middle
This means that cookies, local

00:17:38.246 --> 00:17:39.816 A:middle
storage, and other browsing data

00:17:40.346 --> 00:17:41.726 A:middle
will be contained within your

00:17:42.046 --> 00:17:43.486 A:middle
app and scoped to your app.

00:17:44.816 --> 00:17:46.966 A:middle
And this means that the user

00:17:46.966 --> 00:17:48.526 A:middle
won't automatically be logged in

00:17:48.526 --> 00:17:49.856 A:middle
to whatever accounts they were

00:17:49.856 --> 00:17:51.326 A:middle
logged into in Safari.

00:17:52.006 --> 00:17:54.476 A:middle
What this does is it will

00:17:54.476 --> 00:17:56.456 A:middle
prevent cross-app tracking of

00:17:56.456 --> 00:17:58.496 A:middle
user's browsing activity that

00:17:58.496 --> 00:18:00.216 A:middle
you and your users may not have

00:17:58.496 --> 00:18:00.216 A:middle
you and your users may not have

00:18:00.216 --> 00:18:01.326 A:middle
even been aware about.

00:18:02.006 --> 00:18:04.006 A:middle
And ultimately, it helps keep

00:18:04.006 --> 00:18:06.036 A:middle
users' browsing activity private

00:18:06.306 --> 00:18:08.626 A:middle
and scoped within your app.

00:18:09.846 --> 00:18:11.456 A:middle
Now I'd like to talk about a

00:18:11.456 --> 00:18:13.086 A:middle
change to Private Browsing in

00:18:13.086 --> 00:18:14.266 A:middle
Safari View Controller.

00:18:15.456 --> 00:18:16.826 A:middle
Now that Safari View Controller

00:18:16.826 --> 00:18:19.126 A:middle
has its own separate persistent

00:18:19.126 --> 00:18:21.426 A:middle
data store for each app, it's

00:18:21.426 --> 00:18:23.026 A:middle
browsing mode is no longer tied

00:18:23.026 --> 00:18:25.496 A:middle
to Safari's this means that I

00:18:25.496 --> 00:18:27.206 A:middle
now longer get the following

00:18:27.346 --> 00:18:28.606 A:middle
frustrating experience.

00:18:29.816 --> 00:18:31.576 A:middle
I'm browsing the web in Safari

00:18:31.656 --> 00:18:33.946 A:middle
in Private Mode.

00:18:34.156 --> 00:18:37.236 A:middle
Time passes and later that day

00:18:37.576 --> 00:18:38.866 A:middle
after I've forgotten that I was

00:18:38.866 --> 00:18:41.116 A:middle
even in Private Mode, I go to my

00:18:41.116 --> 00:18:42.886 A:middle
favorite app that opens links

00:18:42.886 --> 00:18:44.296 A:middle
using Safari View Controller.

00:18:45.686 --> 00:18:46.846 A:middle
Safari View Controller is

00:18:46.876 --> 00:18:49.176 A:middle
presented in Private Mode once I

00:18:49.176 --> 00:18:51.306 A:middle
open a link and that's confusing

00:18:51.306 --> 00:18:52.306 A:middle
to me because I didn't

00:18:52.306 --> 00:18:54.116 A:middle
intentionally tell it to open in

00:18:54.116 --> 00:18:55.116 A:middle
Private Browsing Mode.

00:18:56.286 --> 00:18:58.136 A:middle
So, on iOS 11 now that Safari

00:18:58.136 --> 00:18:59.796 A:middle
View Controller has its own

00:19:00.546 --> 00:19:02.496 A:middle
browsing mode, it's no longer

00:19:02.636 --> 00:19:03.726 A:middle
tied to Safari's.

00:19:04.856 --> 00:19:06.556 A:middle
That means that your apps' color

00:19:06.556 --> 00:19:08.446 A:middle
scheme will be used more often.

00:19:08.446 --> 00:19:14.016 A:middle
Now I'd like to tell you about

00:19:14.086 --> 00:19:15.786 A:middle
three new APIs that we've added

00:19:16.236 --> 00:19:17.916 A:middle
so you can really tailor Safari

00:19:17.916 --> 00:19:19.726 A:middle
View Controller to fit your

00:19:20.036 --> 00:19:20.916 A:middle
app's experience.

00:19:22.956 --> 00:19:24.556 A:middle
First I'd like to talk to about

00:19:24.556 --> 00:19:25.926 A:middle
how you can now customize the

00:19:25.926 --> 00:19:27.556 A:middle
Dismiss button of Safari View

00:19:27.556 --> 00:19:28.146 A:middle
Controller.

00:19:28.636 --> 00:19:31.826 A:middle
Language is very important when

00:19:31.826 --> 00:19:33.436 A:middle
conveying intent to the user.

00:19:34.806 --> 00:19:36.176 A:middle
The standard Dismiss button

00:19:36.176 --> 00:19:38.176 A:middle
style for Safari View Controller

00:19:38.246 --> 00:19:38.786 A:middle
is Done.

00:19:39.656 --> 00:19:40.906 A:middle
This works really well for a

00:19:41.006 --> 00:19:42.406 A:middle
standard browsing case, because

00:19:42.406 --> 00:19:43.536 A:middle
the user can browse through a

00:19:43.536 --> 00:19:45.006 A:middle
bunch of different web pages and

00:19:45.236 --> 00:19:46.216 A:middle
then when they're finished

00:19:46.216 --> 00:19:48.166 A:middle
browsing tap Done to indicate

00:19:48.166 --> 00:19:48.876 A:middle
that they've ended their

00:19:48.876 --> 00:19:49.796 A:middle
browsing session.

00:19:51.866 --> 00:19:53.896 A:middle
On iOS 11 we've added two new

00:19:53.896 --> 00:19:55.606 A:middle
options that this Dismiss button

00:19:55.606 --> 00:19:56.386 A:middle
can take on.

00:19:57.286 --> 00:19:58.856 A:middle
The first of those options is

00:19:58.856 --> 00:19:59.416 A:middle
Cancel.

00:20:00.426 --> 00:20:01.926 A:middle
I think Cancel makes a lot of

00:20:01.986 --> 00:20:03.316 A:middle
sense when I'm getting my user's

00:20:03.316 --> 00:20:04.946 A:middle
authenticated to a third-party

00:20:04.946 --> 00:20:05.396 A:middle
service.

00:20:06.386 --> 00:20:07.866 A:middle
The user will know that if they

00:20:07.866 --> 00:20:09.516 A:middle
tap that button, they're not

00:20:09.516 --> 00:20:10.726 A:middle
really authenticating with my

00:20:10.806 --> 00:20:12.336 A:middle
service, they're cancelling the

00:20:12.336 --> 00:20:13.126 A:middle
transaction.

00:20:14.306 --> 00:20:16.336 A:middle
The other new style is Close.

00:20:17.286 --> 00:20:18.356 A:middle
This makes sense if I'm

00:20:18.356 --> 00:20:19.776 A:middle
presenting some transient web

00:20:19.776 --> 00:20:21.646 A:middle
content to the user, perhaps a

00:20:21.646 --> 00:20:23.096 A:middle
Terms of Service page.

00:20:24.336 --> 00:20:25.436 A:middle
I'm giving them a page where

00:20:25.436 --> 00:20:26.486 A:middle
they're probably not likely to

00:20:26.486 --> 00:20:28.316 A:middle
follow other links, so they'll

00:20:28.316 --> 00:20:30.326 A:middle
just Close once they've finished

00:20:30.326 --> 00:20:34.936 A:middle
reading what I've presented to

00:20:35.146 --> 00:20:35.386 A:middle
them.

00:20:35.426 --> 00:20:36.306 A:middle
Now I'd like, or the Dismiss

00:20:36.306 --> 00:20:39.026 A:middle
button style is a property on

00:20:39.226 --> 00:20:40.466 A:middle
SFSafariViewController.

00:20:40.466 --> 00:20:42.966 A:middle
As I mentioned it has these two

00:20:42.966 --> 00:20:43.696 A:middle
new options.

00:20:44.106 --> 00:20:45.586 A:middle
The default style will be Done

00:20:45.896 --> 00:20:46.946 A:middle
but you can choose which ever

00:20:46.946 --> 00:20:48.886 A:middle
style best fits your use case of

00:20:48.886 --> 00:20:50.006 A:middle
Safari View Controller.

00:20:51.546 --> 00:20:52.936 A:middle
The value can even be changed

00:20:52.936 --> 00:20:54.266 A:middle
while Safari View Controller is

00:20:54.266 --> 00:20:55.726 A:middle
presented, which Louie will

00:20:55.726 --> 00:20:56.666 A:middle
demonstrate later.

00:20:56.666 --> 00:21:00.666 A:middle
Now I'd like to talk to you

00:20:56.666 --> 00:21:00.666 A:middle
Now I'd like to talk to you

00:21:00.666 --> 00:21:02.136 A:middle
about a customization you can

00:21:02.136 --> 00:21:03.866 A:middle
make to the Share Sheet in

00:21:03.866 --> 00:21:04.976 A:middle
Safari View Controller.

00:21:07.596 --> 00:21:09.536 A:middle
Let's say I'm presenting a login

00:21:09.566 --> 00:21:10.426 A:middle
flow to the user.

00:21:11.566 --> 00:21:12.946 A:middle
When the tap the share button

00:21:12.946 --> 00:21:13.886 A:middle
they have all these different

00:21:14.006 --> 00:21:15.816 A:middle
actions that they can take, but

00:21:15.816 --> 00:21:16.836 A:middle
some of them don't really make

00:21:16.836 --> 00:21:17.806 A:middle
sense in this case.

00:21:18.646 --> 00:21:19.736 A:middle
They're probably not going to

00:21:19.836 --> 00:21:21.196 A:middle
send the page somewhere else

00:21:21.516 --> 00:21:22.626 A:middle
because it might disrupt the

00:21:22.626 --> 00:21:24.646 A:middle
login flow and the login might

00:21:24.646 --> 00:21:25.726 A:middle
now even work outside of the

00:21:25.726 --> 00:21:26.566 A:middle
context of my app.

00:21:29.006 --> 00:21:31.676 A:middle
Here, I've filtered out, so this

00:21:31.676 --> 00:21:33.786 A:middle
is what the actions that I don't

00:21:33.786 --> 00:21:34.276 A:middle
want to show.

00:21:35.056 --> 00:21:36.796 A:middle
On iOS 11 we're giving the

00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:38.566 A:middle
ability to filter out some of

00:21:38.566 --> 00:21:40.106 A:middle
these UIActivityTypes.

00:21:41.266 --> 00:21:43.896 A:middle
Here, I've filtered out AirDrop,

00:21:44.066 --> 00:21:46.456 A:middle
Mail, and Messages because my

00:21:46.456 --> 00:21:47.926 A:middle
users don't need them in this

00:21:47.926 --> 00:21:48.256 A:middle
case.

00:21:50.346 --> 00:21:52.346 A:middle
You make recognize this API on

00:21:52.346 --> 00:21:53.916 A:middle
UIActivityViewController.

00:21:54.496 --> 00:21:56.816 A:middle
It allows you to set an array of

00:21:56.816 --> 00:21:58.636 A:middle
UIActivityTypes that the user

00:21:58.636 --> 00:22:00.446 A:middle
doesn't need on your

00:21:58.636 --> 00:22:00.446 A:middle
doesn't need on your

00:22:00.446 --> 00:22:01.956 A:middle
UIActivityViewController.

00:22:02.696 --> 00:22:03.626 A:middle
We realize that if you're

00:22:03.626 --> 00:22:05.026 A:middle
implementing your own in-app web

00:22:05.026 --> 00:22:06.636 A:middle
browsing experience, you'd have

00:22:06.636 --> 00:22:08.056 A:middle
the ability to customize the

00:22:08.056 --> 00:22:09.266 A:middle
Share Sheet in this way.

00:22:10.316 --> 00:22:12.076 A:middle
So, in iOS 11 we're exposing

00:22:12.076 --> 00:22:13.546 A:middle
this same ability on

00:22:13.726 --> 00:22:16.576 A:middle
SFSafariViewControllerDelegate

00:22:17.046 --> 00:22:18.846 A:middle
as a method where you can return

00:22:18.846 --> 00:22:21.426 A:middle
an array of UIActivityTypes that

00:22:21.426 --> 00:22:22.846 A:middle
you don't want to be presented

00:22:22.846 --> 00:22:24.806 A:middle
to the user in the context of

00:22:24.806 --> 00:22:26.146 A:middle
your Safari View Controller.

00:22:28.376 --> 00:22:29.806 A:middle
Now, I'd like to talk about Bar

00:22:29.806 --> 00:22:31.366 A:middle
Collapsing in Safari View

00:22:31.366 --> 00:22:31.916 A:middle
Controller.

00:22:33.496 --> 00:22:36.756 A:middle
Safari View Controller's bars

00:22:36.816 --> 00:22:38.426 A:middle
collapse away while in browsing,

00:22:38.886 --> 00:22:39.906 A:middle
which lets me really get

00:22:39.906 --> 00:22:41.356 A:middle
immersed in my browsing

00:22:41.356 --> 00:22:42.086 A:middle
experience.

00:22:43.546 --> 00:22:45.686 A:middle
However, in some cases this bar

00:22:45.686 --> 00:22:46.906 A:middle
collapsing behavior can be

00:22:46.906 --> 00:22:47.586 A:middle
frustrating.

00:22:48.276 --> 00:22:49.836 A:middle
Let's say I have a login flow.

00:22:50.486 --> 00:22:52.316 A:middle
If bars are collapsed, the

00:22:52.316 --> 00:22:54.066 A:middle
Dismiss button gets hidden.

00:22:54.306 --> 00:22:55.676 A:middle
So, it's a bit more difficult to

00:22:55.676 --> 00:22:57.276 A:middle
Dismiss Safari View Controller.

00:22:58.656 --> 00:22:59.766 A:middle
So, in something quick like a

00:22:59.766 --> 00:23:02.806 A:middle
login flow, this standard bar

00:22:59.766 --> 00:23:02.806 A:middle
login flow, this standard bar

00:23:02.806 --> 00:23:04.656 A:middle
collapsing behavior might not

00:23:04.656 --> 00:23:06.636 A:middle
necessarily make sense.

00:23:07.046 --> 00:23:10.276 A:middle
On iOS 11, we're allowing you to

00:23:10.276 --> 00:23:11.476 A:middle
disable this standard bar

00:23:11.476 --> 00:23:12.976 A:middle
collapsing behavior if it best

00:23:13.066 --> 00:23:13.976 A:middle
fits your use case.

00:23:15.436 --> 00:23:17.366 A:middle
This will be a new property on

00:23:17.366 --> 00:23:18.746 A:middle
SFSafariViewController

00:23:18.746 --> 00:23:20.666 A:middle
.Configuration which will be

00:23:20.666 --> 00:23:22.196 A:middle
passed into Safari View

00:23:22.196 --> 00:23:23.656 A:middle
Controller's initializer.

00:23:24.256 --> 00:23:27.246 A:middle
It's best to leave this enabled

00:23:27.596 --> 00:23:29.466 A:middle
if your use case is show user's

00:23:29.506 --> 00:23:31.986 A:middle
browsing, or user's content that

00:23:31.986 --> 00:23:33.206 A:middle
they should really get immersed

00:23:33.286 --> 00:23:33.456 A:middle
in.

00:23:34.236 --> 00:23:35.686 A:middle
But, if it's important to always

00:23:35.686 --> 00:23:37.246 A:middle
have the Dismiss button shown,

00:23:38.076 --> 00:23:39.486 A:middle
you can disable this property.

00:23:39.486 --> 00:23:44.036 A:middle
Now, I'd like to welcome Louie

00:23:44.036 --> 00:23:45.476 A:middle
back to the stage to show you

00:23:45.476 --> 00:23:47.266 A:middle
how easy it is to use these new

00:23:47.266 --> 00:23:49.456 A:middle
APIs to tailor for his app's

00:23:49.456 --> 00:23:50.096 A:middle
experience.

